        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 12 at 11:52AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 1152 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Clayton, or near Tiger, moving north at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mountain City, Lake Rabun, Otto, Rainbow Springs, Long Creek,
Tallulah Falls, Clayton, Tiger, Scaly Mountain, and Sky Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
